rop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/2940200_20250225130746_1.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/2940200_20250225130746_1.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/2940200_20250225130746_1.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/2940200_20250225130746_1.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/2940200_20250225130746_1.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/2940200_20250225130746_1.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Landfall\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn a game with clunkier mechanics, a boss fight with that much to manage could go off the rails, but \u003cem\u003eHaste’s \u003c/em\u003efluidity keeps it on track. Swerving through its levels feels effortless even when you’re not doing so hot, and it rewards you for making risky plays. When everything is going right, it’s like playing a rhythm game where you can’t seem to miss a note. It only breaks the flow when it ends.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eDeveloper Landfall — which released the goofy multiplayer horror game \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=1025X1701642\u0026amp;xs=1\u0026amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fstore.steampowered.com%2Fapp%2F2881650%2FContent_Warning%2F\" rel=\"sponsored\"\u003eContent Warning\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e not that long ago — expects to release \u003cem\u003eHaste: Broken Worlds\u003c/em\u003e sometime later this year.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
